WEBVTT

00:05.500 --> 00:07.625
Previously
on Billions...

00:07.709 --> 00:09.166
Your son.
The gay one.

00:09.250 --> 00:10.750
You sent him to
that religious boot camp

00:10.834 --> 00:13.750
to pray the gay away.

00:13.834 --> 00:15.250
Sweeney quit.

00:15.333 --> 00:17.667
Out of the race
before it even began,

00:17.750 --> 00:20.667
on the heels
of your visit.

00:20.750 --> 00:21.291
Jack.

00:23.333 --> 00:25.750
Will you
make me governor?

00:25.834 --> 00:27.458
His
unwillingness to lie...

00:27.542 --> 00:30.000
His great,
big, sweet heart.

00:30.083 --> 00:31.250
I can use them.

00:31.333 --> 00:32.917
-Ahh.
-Ahh.

00:33.000 --> 00:34.250
Oldest trick in the book.

00:34.333 --> 00:37.083
And if I grant
this request...

00:37.166 --> 00:39.917
There is nothing you can
ask me that I'll refuse you

00:40.000 --> 00:41.583
for the rest of our days.

00:41.667 --> 00:43.125
We're dismissing
the indictment.

00:44.750 --> 00:45.792
Are you
out of danger, too.

00:45.875 --> 00:48.125
That I am.

00:48.208 --> 00:49.959
Now, Mr. Connerty,
as the Axelrod matter is done,

00:50.041 --> 00:53.000
you are free to go
back to the barn.

00:53.083 --> 00:54.000
Go back to Southern?

00:54.083 --> 00:56.834
Be good to have
you back, Bryan.

00:58.208 --> 01:00.500
I really wanted to put on
a show for you tonight.

01:01.792 --> 01:04.500
It felt like we should...

01:10.917 --> 01:15.291
♪ dramatic music ♪

01:15.375 --> 01:18.542
♪♪♪

01:18.625 --> 01:21.250
♪♪♪

01:25.417 --> 01:29.291
...I felt like I was
actually floating...

01:29.375 --> 01:30.709
This morning
when I went running.

01:30.792 --> 01:33.542
Who the hell am I to actually
even go for a morning run?

01:33.625 --> 01:34.959
While I was sleeping in!

01:35.041 --> 01:36.750
You were sleeping like
a bear cub when I left.

01:36.834 --> 01:38.000
I was.

01:38.083 --> 01:40.709
Well, the sleep
of the free.

01:43.375 --> 01:46.625
Now, prepare yourself.

01:46.709 --> 01:49.166
I have something...

01:49.250 --> 01:51.208
very special planned.

01:51.291 --> 01:54.750
And you have earned it.
In every way.

01:54.834 --> 01:56.583
Mm.

01:56.667 --> 01:58.500
I have, indeed.

01:58.583 --> 02:02.208
I was very good
at being bad.

02:02.291 --> 02:04.333
And you are about
to pay for all of it.

02:04.917 --> 02:09.083
I hope that's a promise.

02:09.166 --> 02:13.583
And now address me
as mistress,

02:13.667 --> 02:14.458
if you address
me at all.

02:18.458 --> 02:20.792
Yes, Mistress.

02:22.250 --> 02:23.834
They left me
no choice.

02:25.709 --> 02:28.083
Said they were going to
destroy my business, my life.

02:28.166 --> 02:33.208
I don't think we used
those words, exactly.

02:33.291 --> 02:37.709
Fuck it, Jack. She got
the message, as we intended.

02:37.792 --> 02:40.375
People
usually do.

02:40.458 --> 02:42.041
It's like
we have a gift.

02:43.000 --> 02:44.959
Enough.

02:45.041 --> 02:46.625
Enough. Get to it.

02:46.709 --> 02:49.208
Whatever the fuck
it is.

02:49.291 --> 02:50.709
I'm sorry.

02:50.792 --> 02:52.417
♪ dramatic music ♪

02:52.500 --> 02:54.083
♪♪♪

02:54.166 --> 02:56.000
I'm leaving, too.

02:56.083 --> 02:59.875
No.
Stay a while.

02:59.959 --> 03:02.750
Get comfortable.
"Mistress."

03:06.542 --> 03:08.583
Why don't you take
that coat off, 'ey?

03:08.667 --> 03:10.041
It's hot in here--

03:10.125 --> 03:12.417
Don't you dare talk
to her like that.

03:12.500 --> 03:15.166
Just trying to lighten
the mood, sonny.

03:15.250 --> 03:17.750
No. You're not.
You're gloating.

03:17.834 --> 03:20.542
It's nothing
so arch as that.

03:20.625 --> 03:24.083
This is, um...
this is an object lesson.

03:24.166 --> 03:26.750
And as you know,

03:26.834 --> 03:28.750
people
learn much better

03:28.834 --> 03:32.125
when heightened emotions
accompany the instruction.

03:32.208 --> 03:36.041
♪♪♪

03:36.125 --> 03:41.125
It's time to put away
childish enthusiasms.

03:41.208 --> 03:45.500
Now, what you do at home,
it's your business.

03:45.583 --> 03:48.959
But this,
with a third party,

03:49.041 --> 03:53.500
who we just showed
could be compromised--

03:53.583 --> 03:58.125
a candidate for governor
simply cannot do it.

03:58.208 --> 03:59.792
You didn't do this so we would
have cellular memory.

03:59.875 --> 04:02.291
No. No.

04:02.375 --> 04:05.041
You did it 'cause
it's your kink.

04:05.125 --> 04:08.291
Oh, you think we give
into our appetites

04:08.375 --> 04:10.083
as easily as
you do yours?

04:10.166 --> 04:11.125
Careful, Black Jack.

04:11.208 --> 04:13.750
She might give ya
a crack across the ass.

04:13.834 --> 04:14.959
Get to it.

04:15.041 --> 04:16.333
Time is now, Chuck.

04:16.417 --> 04:21.166
You need to start
raising money. Staffing up.

04:21.250 --> 04:23.917
So we have arranged for you
to meet with Joe Scolari,

04:24.000 --> 04:25.166
our man in Albany.

04:25.250 --> 04:26.667
He will be running
your organization.

04:26.750 --> 04:31.500
♪♪♪

04:31.583 --> 04:33.417
All of this will make
our plans quite public.

04:35.834 --> 04:37.417
And a sitting
United States Attorney

04:37.500 --> 04:40.458
cannot be seen to be
coveting higher public office.

04:40.542 --> 04:43.333
That's why
you need to resign

04:43.417 --> 04:45.959
as United States Attorney.

04:46.041 --> 04:47.208
Hmm?

04:47.291 --> 04:48.917
Right away.

04:49.000 --> 04:51.166
To announce
your intention to run.

04:51.250 --> 04:56.625
♪♪♪

05:00.125 --> 05:02.333
I'm not saying
you can't run.

05:02.417 --> 05:04.083
I've been listening
for three hours.

05:04.166 --> 05:05.583
And that's an awful lot
what it sounds like.

05:05.667 --> 05:07.750
I'm saying you can't
run like this.

05:09.917 --> 05:12.667
If you want to be governor,
that's what I want, too.

05:14.041 --> 05:15.709
But only if you could
do it as you want.

05:15.792 --> 05:16.875
Not as those
two old men want.

05:16.959 --> 05:18.709
And right now they're
setting this thing up

05:18.792 --> 05:20.083
to operate you
like a puppet.

05:20.166 --> 05:21.542
Mm-hmm.

05:23.542 --> 05:25.792
That's what's
bothering you?

05:25.875 --> 05:27.417
What else?

05:27.500 --> 05:30.041
Guilt, Wendy.

05:30.125 --> 05:32.166
We had a narrow escape.

05:32.250 --> 05:34.709
Or we seemed to
for a fleeting moment.

05:34.792 --> 05:39.291
And seeing those two
'old men' shook you.

05:40.166 --> 05:42.291
Made you feel
exposed again.

05:45.000 --> 05:46.500
It might've.

05:49.208 --> 05:51.333
-The things we did...
-Had to do.

05:51.417 --> 05:53.041
Had to do.

05:55.291 --> 05:56.667
But yes, of course.

05:58.208 --> 06:01.917
Blood will have blood.

06:02.000 --> 06:04.166
Maybe this is the time to
step back and deal with that

06:04.250 --> 06:06.583
instead of
charging ahead--

06:06.667 --> 06:08.417
No, ma'am.

06:08.500 --> 06:12.959
The only way is to swallow
that guilt and move forward.

06:13.041 --> 06:15.375
Otherwise that guilt
will swallow us.

06:17.542 --> 06:18.458
And with the governorship,

06:18.542 --> 06:20.542
we can do enough good,
for enough people--

06:20.625 --> 06:23.458
Not if you're enacting
Jack Foley's agenda

06:23.542 --> 06:24.458
of favor trading
and patronage.

06:24.542 --> 06:28.041
He's setting you up
to be his lapdog.

06:28.125 --> 06:29.125
He just showed us
he will snap that leash

06:29.208 --> 06:32.125
whenever he
feels like it.

06:32.208 --> 06:33.792
I won't live that way.

06:35.375 --> 06:38.333
I got to get
the kids going.

06:40.208 --> 06:42.375
But hear this: if
you're moving forward,

06:42.458 --> 06:44.458
you gotta reverse
the power dynamic.

06:44.542 --> 06:45.875
Not easy.

06:45.959 --> 06:47.083
No.

06:48.208 --> 06:49.667
But Foley's hurt
a lot of people.

06:49.750 --> 06:50.792
♪ dramatic music ♪

06:50.875 --> 06:53.291
Find one.

06:53.375 --> 06:55.875
Use one.

06:55.959 --> 06:57.917
Get back on top.

06:58.041 --> 07:00.667
♪♪♪

07:00.750 --> 07:03.208
♪♪♪

07:03.291 --> 07:05.500
Good news people,

07:05.583 --> 07:06.458
thanks to our strategy
coming into focus

07:06.542 --> 07:08.834
over the past few weeks,
the main fund is up.

07:11.250 --> 07:14.417
As our friend Wags might say:
up like his morning wood.

07:14.500 --> 07:15.375
Yes!

07:15.458 --> 07:17.458
Up like his blood
pressure on Cialis...

07:17.542 --> 07:18.500
Amen! Up like the--

07:18.583 --> 07:22.291
Bo-bby! Bo-bby! Bo-bby!

07:22.375 --> 07:25.542
[Black Sabbath's
Never Say Die]

07:25.625 --> 07:30.542
♪ People going nowhere,
taken for a ride ♪

07:30.625 --> 07:35.667
♪ Searching for a reason,
looking for a rhyme ♪

07:35.750 --> 07:37.250
Axe!
Axe! Axe! Axe! Axe!

07:37.333 --> 07:41.709
♪ Snow White's mirror said
"partners in crime!" ♪

07:41.792 --> 07:44.542
♪ Don't they ever
have to worry? ♪

07:45.917 --> 07:47.417
Yeah!

07:47.500 --> 07:49.750
♪ Don't you ever wonder why? ♪

07:52.250 --> 07:54.208
♪ It's a part of me
that tells you ♪

07:54.291 --> 07:57.458
♪ Oh, don't you ever ♪

07:57.542 --> 07:58.834
Yeah!

07:58.917 --> 08:01.583
♪ Don't ever say die ♪

08:01.667 --> 08:02.834
♪ Never, never ♪

08:02.917 --> 08:03.875
Welcome back.

08:03.959 --> 08:04.750
Thanks, buddy.

08:04.834 --> 08:06.834
♪ Never say die again ♪

08:06.917 --> 08:08.250
♪♪♪

08:08.333 --> 08:12.875
O Captain! my Captain!
our fearful trip is done...

08:14.500 --> 08:16.083
Get down from there.

08:22.166 --> 08:23.792
First.

08:23.875 --> 08:26.333
Let's all tip our hats
to Taylor,

08:26.417 --> 08:29.041
who outperformed the benchmarks
by a half point in my absence.

08:29.125 --> 08:30.375
No mean feat...

08:32.959 --> 08:38.583
But, I'm not gonna waste time
now that I got the con back.

08:38.667 --> 08:39.417
I have been thinking
about this moment

08:39.500 --> 08:42.959
since the second
I gave up trading:

08:43.041 --> 08:44.417
Clear the board.

08:44.500 --> 08:46.291
Unwind all current positions.

08:46.375 --> 08:49.166
We will rebuild a new book.

08:49.250 --> 08:51.917
All new positions
will be run through me.

08:52.000 --> 08:52.458
Oww!

08:55.333 --> 08:57.834
Taylor, frag the quant
experiment too.

08:57.917 --> 09:00.458
But, Axe, we've made
some good plays lately

09:00.542 --> 09:02.166
and some of them
are ready to pay out.

09:02.250 --> 09:03.709
This is true.

09:03.792 --> 09:05.542
Guys, I hear you.

09:05.625 --> 09:07.959
All the same:
fresh start.

09:08.041 --> 09:11.291
♪ dramatic music ♪

09:11.375 --> 09:14.041
♪♪♪

09:14.125 --> 09:18.458
♪♪♪

09:18.542 --> 09:21.792
And all is right
with the world again...

09:21.875 --> 09:23.959
You know what
The Beatles did

09:24.041 --> 09:25.208
when they got
back to England

09:25.291 --> 09:27.458
after their first
whirlwind tour of America?

09:27.542 --> 09:29.291
I imagine they all went
to their doctor

09:29.375 --> 09:31.291
and got a shot of penicillin
in their dicks.

09:31.375 --> 09:32.417
Yeah. Sure.
But after that--

09:32.500 --> 09:35.000
They recorded
their next album.

09:35.083 --> 09:38.208
That they did.
One every six months, in fact.

09:38.291 --> 09:39.125
So instead of basking
in their victory,

09:39.208 --> 09:41.250
they consolidated it.

09:41.333 --> 09:42.959
They were young.
And there was only upside

09:43.041 --> 09:44.375
in pressing
their advantage.

09:44.458 --> 09:46.709
There is always only upside
in pressing your advantage.

09:46.792 --> 09:49.417
That's the whole point of
having an advantage to press.

09:49.500 --> 09:50.792
Which we finally do.

09:50.875 --> 09:52.542
So we're getting out
our selling shoes?

09:52.625 --> 09:53.709
Going on a raise.

09:53.792 --> 09:54.667
We're doing
a massive cap raise.

09:54.750 --> 09:58.583
And quickly.
Twenty bill within six months.

09:58.667 --> 10:00.667
But we position
ourselves as the buyer.

10:00.750 --> 10:04.041
We make them beg us
to take their money.

10:04.125 --> 10:06.000
Just like we did
back in 2015.

10:06.083 --> 10:08.000
This isn't then.

10:08.083 --> 10:11.083
That's not a very
Wendy thing to say...

10:11.166 --> 10:12.291
-But accurate.
-Look.

10:12.375 --> 10:15.333
This will be good for all of us.
Especially you, Taylor.

10:15.417 --> 10:17.125
You've never
been on a raise.

10:17.208 --> 10:18.917
This is the other
half of the job.

10:19.000 --> 10:21.500
And the results that we've
generated are the seeds.

10:21.583 --> 10:23.917
And the horseshit we will
spew is the fertilizer.

10:24.000 --> 10:25.125
Horseshit works.

10:25.208 --> 10:27.375
But it doesn't
get rid of the weeds.

10:27.458 --> 10:28.709
By which you mean
our recent history.

10:28.792 --> 10:32.333
Our legal troubles.
All of which are in the past.

10:32.417 --> 10:34.166
I'm saying if I were on
the other side of the table,

10:34.250 --> 10:36.959
I'd have questions.
And reservations.

10:37.041 --> 10:39.125
Where's the rah rah shit
to counter this?

10:39.208 --> 10:41.959
I'm not sure that's
what's required.

10:42.041 --> 10:43.083
Taylor, when you
come with us,

10:43.166 --> 10:46.375
you will see that this man
parries those questions

10:46.458 --> 10:48.208
like Charles Van Doren.

10:48.291 --> 10:49.709
Van Doren was
fed the answers.

10:49.792 --> 10:51.542
But he got the money.
As will we.

10:51.625 --> 10:53.542
And that's all
that matters.

10:53.625 --> 10:56.041
I'll get you
the old pitch books.

10:56.125 --> 10:57.375
You can work from there
on new stuff.

10:57.458 --> 11:02.083
♪ tense music ♪

11:04.458 --> 11:05.083
You okay?

11:05.166 --> 11:06.792
Mostly.

11:08.291 --> 11:11.083
Not really.

11:11.166 --> 11:12.959
I think I need to use your guys
to deal with something.

11:13.041 --> 11:16.250
-If you need me to, I will.

11:16.333 --> 11:18.750
But I'd prefer to
keep it to myself.

11:18.834 --> 11:20.417
It involves family.

11:20.500 --> 11:22.583
Yes. Absolutely.

11:22.667 --> 11:24.333
I'll get them to
give what you need.

11:24.417 --> 11:26.583
But it's not 'them' anymore.
Hall's back.

11:26.667 --> 11:30.583
♪♪♪

11:30.667 --> 11:32.208
♪ dramatic music ♪

11:35.166 --> 11:39.250
♪♪♪

11:48.166 --> 11:49.750
Hi.

11:57.542 --> 12:00.041
Have to go.

12:00.125 --> 12:02.458
♪ tense music ♪

12:02.542 --> 12:04.291
You're in here now.

12:04.375 --> 12:08.041
♪♪♪

12:08.125 --> 12:10.959
♪♪♪

12:12.208 --> 12:14.125
So, you don't have
server access yet.

12:14.208 --> 12:16.625
Your authorization's
underway.

12:16.709 --> 12:18.458
What am I
supposed to do?

12:18.542 --> 12:21.291
Await instructions.

12:21.375 --> 12:23.542
Chuck will be
with you shortly.

12:23.625 --> 12:26.959
♪♪♪

12:27.041 --> 12:30.250
♪♪♪

12:30.333 --> 12:33.750
♪♪♪

12:33.834 --> 12:36.250
♪♪♪

12:36.333 --> 12:40.583
♪♪♪

12:40.667 --> 12:43.166
I love owning
the Flemish school,

12:43.250 --> 12:46.000
but it is tough to hang
in a PoMo townhouse.

12:48.000 --> 12:49.667
My wife says
the Dutch Masters

12:49.750 --> 12:51.333
don't go with
the De Sede couch.

12:51.417 --> 12:52.709
She's young.

12:52.792 --> 12:53.792
She is indeed...

12:53.875 --> 12:56.542
Look, Bobby, now that
we're together,

12:56.625 --> 12:59.208
let me congratulate
you in person.

12:59.291 --> 13:01.500
I hope you got the bottle
of Armand de Brignac.

13:01.583 --> 13:03.083
I did. Thanks.

13:03.166 --> 13:05.041
I always knew you were
falsely charged.

13:05.125 --> 13:07.250
I hope you know I was doing
everything I could

13:07.333 --> 13:08.417
from the inside.

13:08.500 --> 13:10.834
Of course.
I felt you.

13:10.917 --> 13:12.333
Score one
for the good guys.

13:12.417 --> 13:13.208
Yeah.

13:13.291 --> 13:15.333
Well.

13:15.417 --> 13:16.041
-Hmm.
-So, get to it.

13:18.583 --> 13:21.125
Well, you know I'm committed
to my government post.

13:21.208 --> 13:22.709
The sense of service.

13:22.792 --> 13:23.667
The good I'm doing
for the country

13:23.750 --> 13:26.458
as the Secretary
of the Treasury--

13:26.542 --> 13:27.792
We're all sleeping
a lot better

13:27.875 --> 13:29.083
knowing you're watching
over the markets--

13:29.166 --> 13:34.291
But, I do like to keep an eye
peeled for opportunities.

13:36.417 --> 13:38.458
In this case?

13:38.542 --> 13:40.875
Natural gas.

13:40.959 --> 13:44.417
You know regulation has been
strangling the sector.

13:44.500 --> 13:46.000
You know
something different?

13:46.083 --> 13:47.375
I know many, many things

13:47.458 --> 13:50.250
thanks to my proximity
to the FERC.

13:50.333 --> 13:52.208
But what I need

13:52.291 --> 13:55.125
is someone who can act
on the information.

13:58.500 --> 14:01.583
Todd, I would
never trade

14:01.667 --> 14:03.083
on privileged,
non-public information.

14:03.166 --> 14:06.500
And I hope whatever audio
or video recording devices

14:06.583 --> 14:08.000
running in here right now

14:08.083 --> 14:10.834
have me saying
that loud and clear.

14:10.917 --> 14:12.417
You've got it wrong.

14:12.500 --> 14:13.917
Do I?

14:14.000 --> 14:15.959
Look, I just got out of
the government's fucking web.

14:16.041 --> 14:18.125
I'm not walking back
into it thanks to you.

14:18.208 --> 14:20.083
I knew you'd be
reluctant to trust me.

14:20.166 --> 14:23.750
That you would need some sort
of proof of my intent.

14:23.834 --> 14:26.875
♪ dramatic music ♪

14:26.959 --> 14:28.709
Security Bank
of Grand Cayman.

14:28.792 --> 14:30.417
This is the bank--
one of them--

14:30.500 --> 14:31.667
where I still have
my offshore accounts.

14:31.750 --> 14:34.792
DC doesn't know about it,
of course.

14:34.875 --> 14:37.709
Nor do they know
that I'm telling you

14:37.792 --> 14:40.000
that the EPA is about
to rescind a certain regulation

14:40.083 --> 14:43.625
that will prop up
the entire natural gas space.

14:43.709 --> 14:46.583
♪♪♪

14:46.667 --> 14:47.709
Hmm?

14:47.792 --> 14:50.458
I'll give you
the details.

14:50.542 --> 14:53.417
Take the account information
and give me my piece in crypto.

14:53.500 --> 14:56.417
♪♪♪

14:56.500 --> 14:59.333
♪♪♪

15:01.625 --> 15:04.959
♪♪♪

15:05.041 --> 15:06.667
I'll see you soon, Bobby.

15:06.750 --> 15:10.667
♪♪♪

15:12.041 --> 15:15.291
Kate, can you at least tell me
when Chuck's gonna see me?

15:17.542 --> 15:21.208
♪ funky music ♪

15:21.291 --> 15:23.625
♪♪♪

15:23.709 --> 15:26.875
♪♪♪

