The hiring of:
a campaign manager,

15:37.959 --> 15:39.667
a head of comms,
a body person--

15:39.750 --> 15:42.834
Do I have any say in this?

15:43.583 --> 15:45.834
The success
of your campaign

15:45.917 --> 15:48.834
is of the
utmost importance...

15:48.917 --> 15:52.125
I can see how effective
that must be.

15:52.208 --> 15:55.542
But before you go on,
let me say

15:55.625 --> 15:58.667
that I'm ready to follow
your collective lead.

15:58.750 --> 16:00.041
I'm willing not merely
to stoop to conquer,

16:00.125 --> 16:02.583
I will breaststroke
through offal to do it.

16:06.291 --> 16:07.625
Good.

16:07.709 --> 16:09.542
So to get
things started,

16:09.625 --> 16:12.000
you'll announce from
an event at your home

16:12.083 --> 16:13.542
in the next few days.

16:13.625 --> 16:16.000
Trot the wife and kids
out in front of the cameras.

16:16.083 --> 16:18.834
And time it
with your resignation.

16:22.125 --> 16:23.792
So, you say I'm looking
good downstate.

16:23.875 --> 16:25.875
-Mm-hmm.

16:25.959 --> 16:28.375
Well, Bob Sweeney,
in Buffalo.

16:28.458 --> 16:30.709
I know you two have
had your problems--

16:30.792 --> 16:33.375
capped off by that wicked
J-Block you put on him.

16:35.458 --> 16:36.583
That a political term?

16:36.667 --> 16:37.959
Roller derby.

16:38.041 --> 16:41.125
I was a fan growing up.

16:41.208 --> 16:43.917
Big, strong women
in fishnets, you know?

16:44.000 --> 16:47.583
Oh, I do. Yeah.

16:48.875 --> 16:52.750
Anyway...you need
Buffalo now,

16:52.834 --> 16:56.417
which means you need
Bob Sweeney.

16:56.500 --> 16:59.208
You need to make it right,
bring him into the fold.

16:59.291 --> 17:01.500
You think Foley could help
grease the skids with him

17:01.583 --> 17:02.583
-Nah.

17:05.000 --> 17:09.375
Foley tossed Sweeney aside
when you became favorite son

17:09.458 --> 17:11.000
and he feels burned.

17:13.000 --> 17:15.125
That's gonna be on you...

17:18.583 --> 17:20.917
For you.

17:21.000 --> 17:24.000
You'll look good in it
up in Hudson on weekends.

17:24.083 --> 17:25.458
It's not for sale.

17:25.542 --> 17:27.000
Oh, everything's
for sale.

17:27.083 --> 17:29.583
-I'm not that easy to buy off.
-I'm not trying to.

17:29.667 --> 17:31.625
I just thought you could
use a little love.

17:31.709 --> 17:34.125
You did a lot of good work
under tough conditions.

17:34.208 --> 17:35.375
This is not about ego.

17:35.458 --> 17:37.458
It's about acting
rationally. Logically.

17:37.542 --> 17:38.959
Like my quant project,
for instance.

17:39.041 --> 17:40.375
I'd really like to
keep them on until--

17:40.458 --> 17:42.000
Broom them,
like I told you.

17:42.083 --> 17:43.917
You cleared the entirety
of our positions--

17:44.000 --> 17:45.792
our successful,
money-making positions--

17:45.875 --> 17:48.083
right before asking people
to trust you with outside money.

17:48.166 --> 17:49.750
Won't that look like
erratic behavior?

17:49.834 --> 17:52.583
No, it'll look like we're
putting our best foot forward.

17:52.667 --> 17:55.041
And you're getting paid,
so you shouldn't worry about it.

17:55.125 --> 17:55.375
Forget the car.

17:58.458 --> 17:59.667
I want my own book.

17:59.750 --> 18:01.250
A billion dollars.
To manage, unencumbered.

18:01.333 --> 18:05.166
You took your ball back.
Give me something of my own.

18:05.250 --> 18:05.625
♪ mid-tempo music ♪

18:05.709 --> 18:08.667
Fine. Done...

18:09.750 --> 18:12.333
So you don't want
the car? Let's go.

18:12.417 --> 18:12.750
No.

18:12.834 --> 18:16.333
♪♪♪

18:16.417 --> 18:16.709
I'll take that, too.

18:16.792 --> 18:21.291
♪♪♪

18:21.375 --> 18:23.333
Thank you for
seeing me, Mayor Sweeney.

18:29.792 --> 18:32.583
What now, Chuck?

18:32.667 --> 18:35.041
You already turned me
into political roadkill.

18:35.125 --> 18:37.500
You here to
back over me now?

18:37.583 --> 18:40.667
Not like that.
I'm here to move forward.

18:40.750 --> 18:43.667
To salve the wounds
of the past.

18:51.083 --> 18:54.166
You want my support now.

18:54.250 --> 18:54.875
Of course.

18:54.959 --> 18:57.542
Timing makes sense.

18:57.625 --> 19:00.000
Well, know this: since
Foley turned away from me,

19:00.083 --> 19:03.583
my future has...dimmed.

19:03.667 --> 19:06.083
I'm a crippled mayor
with no route upward.

19:06.166 --> 19:08.667
Let me do for you then.
All right?

19:08.750 --> 19:10.917
First: this.

19:14.125 --> 19:17.208
Your son's confessional,
about how you mistreated him.

19:17.291 --> 19:19.542
It's my only copy.

19:19.625 --> 19:22.542
It was wrong of me to have
played it in the first place.

19:34.667 --> 19:35.875
Good.

19:35.959 --> 19:39.083
As they say on the game shows:
But that's not all.

19:40.750 --> 19:42.333
I will revive
your fortunes.

19:42.417 --> 19:44.750
Your opponent
in the next election?

19:44.834 --> 19:47.000
He's about to find himself
under indictment.

19:47.083 --> 19:49.125
By my office.

19:49.208 --> 19:50.625
You'd do that for me?

19:50.709 --> 19:54.291
In exchange for some help
with Jack Foley.

19:54.375 --> 19:54.667
♪ dramatic music ♪

19:54.750 --> 19:56.959
Really?

19:57.041 --> 19:58.166
His thumb
pressing down on me

19:58.250 --> 19:59.750
like I'm an insect--
I don't like it.

19:59.834 --> 20:02.542
♪♪♪

20:02.625 --> 20:03.917
It's a ballsy
move, Chuck.

20:04.000 --> 20:07.417
Well, there is no move unless
you have something for me.

20:07.500 --> 20:09.000
You know him
better than I do.

20:09.083 --> 20:13.959
♪♪♪

20:14.041 --> 20:18.792
♪♪♪

20:18.875 --> 20:20.458
You have to keep me
out of this.

20:22.041 --> 20:23.417
I may not have
his friendship anymore,

20:23.500 --> 20:25.041
but I definitely don't
need him as an enemy.

20:25.125 --> 20:26.792
Nothing will
stick to you.

20:26.875 --> 20:29.792
♪♪♪

20:29.875 --> 20:31.750
On the square?

20:31.834 --> 20:34.208
♪♪♪

20:34.291 --> 20:37.458
From one traveling man
to another.

20:37.542 --> 20:40.625
♪♪♪

20:40.709 --> 20:43.458
I got The Beatles
on my mind again.

20:43.542 --> 20:45.166
Because he's about
to become Pete Best?

20:45.250 --> 20:47.458
I was thinking
more of another one.

20:48.917 --> 20:50.291
Phew.

20:50.375 --> 20:53.333
I felt so charged
with Axe Cap-thusiasm

20:53.417 --> 20:54.333
after yesterday's meeting

20:54.417 --> 20:59.083
that I wrote a check
to the foundation for 4k.

20:59.166 --> 21:01.250
I trust that Ayles will put
that thing to good use.

21:01.333 --> 21:02.583
He will.
Though, in truth,

21:02.667 --> 21:04.291
you might've saved it
for gas money.

21:04.375 --> 21:05.500
Hah. If I stressed
about gas money,

21:05.583 --> 21:08.458
I'd've never gotten the car
in the first place...

21:11.709 --> 21:13.125
Uh,

21:13.208 --> 21:15.625
I sense
a disturbance in the force.

21:15.709 --> 21:19.667
Do you know whose life has
always amazed me, Spyros?

21:19.750 --> 21:21.834
George Harrison's.

21:21.917 --> 21:22.667
Ah, that Beatle.

21:22.750 --> 21:24.834
Yes.

21:24.917 --> 21:27.333
Because Harrison
wasn't only a Beatle.

21:27.417 --> 21:29.625
He was also
a Traveling Wilbury.

21:29.709 --> 21:32.333
And it was no mean feat
to be a Wilbury.

21:32.417 --> 21:34.709
Legends only
need apply.

21:34.792 --> 21:37.542
Dylan and Petty used to
make a game of it, in fact.

21:37.625 --> 21:39.375
They used to throw a name
out there, and decide,

21:39.458 --> 21:43.208
in an instant, if that person
was or was not a Wilbury.

21:43.291 --> 21:45.709
It required some
ineffable combination

21:45.792 --> 21:48.250
of wit, cool,
and credibility.

21:48.333 --> 21:50.834
Like Jack Nicholson,
for example.

21:50.917 --> 21:51.834
Wilbury.

21:51.917 --> 21:52.709
Richard Dreyfuss--

21:52.792 --> 21:56.000
-Great actor--
-But not a Wilbury.

21:57.208 --> 22:00.000
And you Spyros.
It has become clear.

22:00.083 --> 22:02.542
Are not a Wilbury.

22:05.625 --> 22:07.542
But I am!

22:07.625 --> 22:09.375
I am a Wilbury.

22:09.458 --> 22:09.875
I can prove it
to you. I--

22:09.959 --> 22:11.792
You're fired.

22:11.875 --> 22:13.250
You're firing me?

22:13.333 --> 22:16.041
I just did. It happened.
I said the words.

22:16.125 --> 22:18.709
Long time coming.

22:18.792 --> 22:20.792
But that Wendy thing
worked out.

22:20.875 --> 22:24.375
-So there's no reason--
-Nothing you can say or do.

22:24.458 --> 22:25.583
♪ dramatic music ♪

22:25.667 --> 22:27.417
You might have done your job,
but you have failed

22:27.500 --> 22:28.583
to provide
additional value.

22:28.667 --> 22:32.125
And you've ostracized
the entire company.

22:32.208 --> 22:35.041
I'll prove it to you.
I-I-I do have value.

22:35.125 --> 22:37.500
I-I am a Wilbury.

22:37.583 --> 22:40.000
I'm all the Wilburys.
Put together.

22:40.083 --> 22:42.250
♪♪♪

22:42.333 --> 22:43.750
I feel
five years younger.

22:44.250 --> 22:47.208
♪♪♪

22:49.500 --> 22:50.917
♪♪♪

22:54.750 --> 22:59.125
Oh, I've been having
wet dreams about this moment.

23:00.125 --> 23:01.375
-Bill.

23:01.458 --> 23:04.291
-We've had our issues--
-Mm...

23:04.375 --> 23:08.041
--But I have a play,
virgin intel.

23:08.125 --> 23:09.542
Your kind of thing.

23:09.625 --> 23:11.083
Nah. Real shame.

23:11.166 --> 23:13.291
I only talk ideas

23:13.375 --> 23:16.333
with current employees
of Axe Capital.

23:17.083 --> 23:20.542
This is the
Clarence Beeks shit,

23:20.625 --> 23:23.709
but I guess you don't
want to hear about it.

23:23.792 --> 23:27.375
♪♪♪

23:27.458 --> 23:30.208
♪♪♪

23:30.291 --> 23:32.333
The coffee gear
is company-owned.

23:32.417 --> 23:35.125
Make sure
he leaves that behind.

23:35.208 --> 23:36.917
♪♪♪

23:37.000 --> 23:40.333
♪♪♪

23:40.417 --> 23:43.625
Whoo!

23:43.709 --> 23:45.166
Buh-bye!

23:45.250 --> 23:49.917
♪♪♪

23:50.000 --> 23:52.500
♪♪♪

23:52.583 --> 23:57.291
♪♪♪

23:57.375 --> 24:02.000
♪♪♪

24:02.083 --> 24:05.959
♪♪♪

24:06.041 --> 24:09.709
♪♪♪

24:11.208 --> 24:15.959
♪♪♪

24:16.041 --> 24:20.041
♪♪♪

24:20.125 --> 24:24.875
♪♪♪

24:24.959 --> 24:30.667
♪♪♪

24:33.166 --> 24:35.166
I'll take it from here.

24:44.625 --> 24:46.041
You have thirty seconds.

24:47.709 --> 24:50.291
I can still access a list
of all the public companies

24:50.375 --> 24:52.208
being investigated
by the SEC,

24:52.291 --> 24:53.875
but have not disclosed
the investigation

24:53.959 --> 24:55.125
to their shareholders.

24:56.625 --> 24:59.458
With your...special
brand of knowledge,

24:59.542 --> 25:02.166
you can determine which
of these inquiries have teeth

25:02.250 --> 25:04.542
and which are bullshit.

25:04.625 --> 25:05.625
You can short the companies
that you think will go down

25:05.709 --> 25:08.083
when the investigations
come to light--

25:08.166 --> 25:09.959
And go long on those that
get dinged by the bad press

25:10.041 --> 25:10.792
from being looked into,
and shoot up

25:10.875 --> 25:13.125
when they're
ultimately cleared.

25:13.208 --> 25:14.625
Right Said Fred.

25:20.917 --> 25:22.417
Okay.

25:23.333 --> 25:25.875
I like what I hear.

25:25.959 --> 25:28.083
Other than that
Right Said Fred bullshit.

25:33.667 --> 25:35.333
Hey, team.

25:36.041 --> 25:38.208
Tough news.

25:38.291 --> 25:39.792
Gonna need you to
back it up and shut it down.

25:43.333 --> 25:45.834
Take down the paper on
the windows before you go...

25:53.041 --> 25:54.458
Lara.

25:54.542 --> 25:57.625
-Hi, Dad.

25:57.709 --> 25:59.166
I'm taking him
to the dentist,

25:59.250 --> 26:01.041
but I had to come by
to straighten something out.

26:01.125 --> 26:02.166
Oh

26:02.250 --> 26:03.709
This 2 and 20
fee charge

26:03.792 --> 26:06.375
has got to be some sort
of clerical error, Bobby.

26:06.458 --> 26:10.208
No error.
It's no longer my money.

26:10.291 --> 26:12.458
The fees go to Axe Cap's
hard-working employees

26:12.542 --> 26:14.542
who ensure
your returns.

26:15.166 --> 26:17.875
Seriously?

26:17.959 --> 26:18.917
If I'm paying retail

26:19.000 --> 26:21.291
I may as well yank it out
and spread it around--

26:21.375 --> 26:22.208
Calm down.

26:22.291 --> 26:25.041
Gord, hang here a sec.
Lara, with me...

26:37.417 --> 26:39.417
Look, you can move
your money if you want.

26:39.500 --> 26:41.709
But if you want me to
manage it, this is the cost.

26:41.792 --> 26:44.166
Didn't you read the agreement?
Didn't Birch read it?

26:49.750 --> 26:51.208
Gordie!

26:51.291 --> 26:52.500
Hi, Aunt Wendy.

26:52.583 --> 26:54.041
Hey.

26:54.125 --> 26:55.458
What's going on?

26:55.542 --> 26:57.750
Mom and Dad are
having a smackdown.

26:57.834 --> 26:59.333
Smackdown?

26:59.417 --> 27:01.125
What Mom calls a fight.

27:01.208 --> 27:03.208
Hmm.

27:03.291 --> 27:04.333
Sit, sweetie.

27:04.417 --> 27:06.542
After all the nice talk,

27:06.625 --> 27:08.333
this is the truth of it:
you're pissed

27:08.417 --> 27:10.917
and you're being vindictive,
that I got half your money.

27:11.000 --> 27:14.250
I may be vindictive,
but it's not over that.

27:14.333 --> 27:16.375
You threatened to take
my kids across the country

27:16.458 --> 27:17.834
while I rotted in jail--

27:17.917 --> 27:20.375
I was trying
to look out for them.

27:20.458 --> 27:23.917
This is something
we don't come back from.

27:24.000 --> 27:26.291
Instead of focusing on
what fees you're paying,

27:26.375 --> 27:28.625
I suggest you focus
on the money you're making.

27:28.709 --> 27:29.667
How you'll spend it.

27:29.750 --> 27:31.750
What your life will be
like going forward.

27:31.834 --> 27:33.500
Because that's
what I'm doing.

27:33.583 --> 27:35.917
♪ dramatic music ♪

27:36.000 --> 27:38.166
[indistinct conversations
in distance]

27:38.250 --> 27:41.291
♪♪♪

27:41.375 --> 27:44.375
♪♪♪

27:44.458 --> 27:46.667
♪♪♪

27:46.750 --> 27:50.125
...So they say to us:
it's not your fault,

27:50.208 --> 27:52.834
it's something that happened
between Mommy and Daddy.

27:52.917 --> 27:54.333
-That's right.
-I know.

27:54.417 --> 27:57.291
But Dean and I didn't even
think it was our fault--

27:57.375 --> 27:57.917
until they started
saying that...

27:58.000 --> 28:00.333
Hmm.

28:01.333 --> 28:03.709
The thing you need to understand
is: you are not your parents.

28:03.792 --> 28:04.625
-You are--
-Who the hell gave you

28:04.709 --> 28:07.583
permission to talk
to my son.

28:09.291 --> 28:11.417
Gordie! Wait outside.

28:12.500 --> 28:15.125
You should listen to
your mother. Go, sweetie.

28:15.667 --> 28:17.333
Thanks, Aunt Wendy.

28:17.417 --> 28:19.166
Don't call her that.
She is not family!

28:20.500 --> 28:23.875
The men in my life don't need
any more of your fucking advice.

28:23.959 --> 28:25.458
I think you might be
in a place

28:25.542 --> 28:28.375
where you can't even recognize
when someone is trying to help.

28:28.458 --> 28:31.500
No. I can recognize
your intention.

28:31.583 --> 28:33.125
But when I look at Bobby,

28:33.208 --> 28:35.875
it's the results that seem
all fucked up to me.

28:35.959 --> 28:38.959
♪ tense music ♪

28:39.041 --> 28:42.125
♪♪♪

28:42.208 --> 28:46.291
♪♪♪

28:46.375 --> 28:50.458
♪♪♪

28:53.333 --> 28:55.041
♪♪♪

29:01.041 --> 29:04.917
I bet you don't
even cheat at that, do you?

29:07.041 --> 29:09.125
-Never saw the point.
-Sure.

29:09.208 --> 29:12.667
Yeah, what do they say:
You'd only be cheating yourself.

29:12.750 --> 29:15.000
Doesn't matter, boss.

29:15.083 --> 29:17.375
If you show me a move
or two to gain advantage,

29:17.458 --> 29:18.583
I'll try 'em.

29:18.667 --> 29:20.458
Well, that's new!

29:21.333 --> 29:24.834
Open to change.

29:24.917 --> 29:26.000
Good.

29:26.083 --> 29:28.250
Come on, let's get you
an office befitting.

29:35.166 --> 29:36.041
-Thank you.
-Mm.

29:36.125 --> 29:38.959
I-I thought you were
sending me to Siberia.

29:39.041 --> 29:40.667
There's no need to worry
about any of that.

29:40.750 --> 29:43.166
About hard feelings
or retribution.

29:43.250 --> 29:47.166
No, you did everything
exactly the way I taught you.

29:47.250 --> 29:50.166
Investigated the case fully,
followed where it led,

29:50.250 --> 29:52.625
and refused to be
cowed by power.

29:52.709 --> 29:54.792
That's more
than admirable.

29:54.875 --> 29:56.250
It's heroic.

29:58.250 --> 30:00.709
-I had the best teacher. You.

30:00.792 --> 30:02.125
Thanks for
seeing it this way.

30:02.208 --> 30:05.125
I worried maybe
you'd hold a grudge--

30:05.208 --> 30:06.208
Grudge?

30:06.291 --> 30:09.083
Nossir. No.

30:09.166 --> 30:10.417
No, you said
it yourself.

30:10.500 --> 30:12.875
None of this
is personal.

30:12.959 --> 30:14.709
-Hm.
-Yeah, Bryan.

30:14.792 --> 30:17.667
You learned every lesson
I had to teach.

30:18.583 --> 30:20.083
Except the one
that matters most.

30:23.542 --> 30:25.000
You didn't win.

30:26.458 --> 30:28.709
Didn't finish me off.

30:28.792 --> 30:31.166
♪ dramatic music ♪

30:31.250 --> 30:33.166
No, I'm still standing here
in the best job there is

30:33.250 --> 30:38.917
because I can do what I want,
when I want, how I want.

30:39.000 --> 30:42.875
Oh, I am
bad, bad Leroy Brown.

30:42.959 --> 30:45.208
Baddest man in
the whole damn town.

30:45.291 --> 30:47.917
-Just wait a second--
-You breached my threshold

30:48.000 --> 30:50.667
and threatened me,

30:50.750 --> 30:53.417
threatened my wife,
the mother of my children.

30:53.500 --> 30:56.083
♪♪♪

30:56.166 --> 30:57.750
How could you think
there's a universe

30:57.834 --> 31:01.291
where you would
survive that?

31:02.792 --> 31:04.250
Oh, Bryan.

31:04.333 --> 31:06.250
You are many things.

31:06.333 --> 31:08.417
♪♪♪

31:08.500 --> 31:10.333
A man. A boy.

31:10.417 --> 31:12.917
A lawyer. A fighter.

31:13.000 --> 31:15.125
A student of the dark side
of humanity.

31:15.208 --> 31:17.166
And a lover
of jurisprudence.

31:17.250 --> 31:20.792
But there's one thing
you're certainly not.

31:20.875 --> 31:22.875
An Assistant
United States Attorney

31:22.959 --> 31:25.125
for the Southern District
of New York.

31:25.208 --> 31:27.291
Drop your credentials
at the guard's desk.

31:27.375 --> 31:31.166
And GET THE FUCK
OUT OF HERE!

31:46.583 --> 31:48.750
Here endeth the lesson.

31:51.041 --> 31:53.375
[telephone rings,
indistinct conversations]

31:56.041 --> 31:59.875
♪ dramatic music ♪

31:59.959 --> 32:03.333
♪♪♪

32:03.417 --> 32:08.125
♪♪♪

32:08.208 --> 32:11.667
♪♪♪

32:11.750 --> 32:13.208
You told me to clear
the positions.

32:13.291 --> 32:14.834
I didn't just clear
twenty-five percent of them.

32:14.917 --> 32:16.500
You told me
to broom the quants.

32:16.583 --> 32:18.000
I didn't just get
rid of a quarter of them.

32:18.083 --> 32:19.667
I told you you'd get
the billion.

32:19.750 --> 32:21.500
I didn't tell you when.

32:21.583 --> 32:24.291
You are CIO.
It's an advisory role.

32:24.375 --> 32:25.917
So some oversight
is necessary.

32:26.000 --> 32:28.041
You're going to oversee
my investments?

32:28.125 --> 32:29.458
Call them suggestions.

32:29.542 --> 32:32.250
And I'd like yours
on buying a basket

32:32.333 --> 32:34.333
of natural gas names
and pipeline companies.

32:34.417 --> 32:36.375
Then my suggestion
is: don't.

32:36.458 --> 32:37.667
Regulations are
too unpredictable

32:37.750 --> 32:38.875
and are hampering
the industry.

32:38.959 --> 32:40.583
What do you know about
upcoming announcements

32:40.667 --> 32:41.917
that might
mitigate that?

32:42.000 --> 32:43.083
I don't
know anything.

32:43.166 --> 32:44.291
Because I don't work
in the government.

32:47.417 --> 32:48.125
But you know something.

32:48.208 --> 32:50.083
About a coming ruling.
From inside?

32:52.250 --> 32:55.917
Why don't you make the play,
jumpstart your new book.

32:56.000 --> 32:58.792
Keep it.
I'll come up with my own.

32:58.875 --> 32:59.667
Suit yourself.

32:59.750 --> 33:01.625
You can lead a horse
to natural gas

33:01.709 --> 33:03.500
but you can't
make it invest.

33:03.583 --> 33:05.709
I question why you're
making this kind of move.

33:05.792 --> 33:06.875
Not based on analysis,

33:06.959 --> 33:09.792
but rather on
unsubstantiated information.

33:09.875 --> 33:12.208
Is it because of the raise?
Wanting to look prescient?

33:12.291 --> 33:13.917
It's about the future
of Axe Capital,

33:14.000 --> 33:16.500
making it what
it's supposed to be.

33:16.583 --> 33:17.500
What's that?

33:17.583 --> 33:18.834
Unassailable.

33:18.917 --> 33:21.875
Untouchable. Unbreakable.

33:21.959 --> 33:24.750
An institution
that's TBTF-W--

33:24.834 --> 33:26.542
too big to fuck with.

33:26.625 --> 33:28.375
♪ tense music ♪

33:28.458 --> 33:30.291
Do you know
how you sound?

33:30.375 --> 33:32.041
Yeah.

33:32.125 --> 33:33.041
Certain.

33:33.125 --> 33:36.834
♪♪♪

33:36.917 --> 33:39.458
♪♪♪

33:41.291 --> 33:44.208
[Chuck Prophet's
"Ford Econoline"]

33:44.291 --> 33:46.000
I would be
looking at Telemarket.

33:46.083 --> 33:50.500
I met their chairman once,
and he was very sweaty.

33:50.583 --> 33:52.041
There's something
guilty there.

33:52.125 --> 33:53.041
No. Guy who gets
that sweaty

33:53.125 --> 33:56.250
talking to the SEC
is not guilty.

33:56.333 --> 33:59.125
He's neurotic.
And a loser.

33:59.208 --> 34:00.291
But not a cheat.

34:00.375 --> 34:02.250
♪♪♪

34:02.333 --> 34:05.875
It's like you have a seventh
sense for the dark side.

34:05.959 --> 34:06.709
Sixth sense?

34:06.792 --> 34:08.291
I try to avoid cliché.

34:12.250 --> 34:14.291
Don't worry.
I'll manage the caterers.

34:14.375 --> 34:17.333
I'll send them over
when you're at your "work."

34:17.417 --> 34:19.417
You say work as though
it's a sin.

34:19.500 --> 34:22.792
So tomorrow we are
gonna get this horse

34:22.875 --> 34:24.333
into the goddamned race.

34:24.417 --> 34:26.166
I'm so glad, you're back
from your trip, Ellen.

34:26.250 --> 34:27.583
And will be able
to be here for it.

34:27.667 --> 34:29.792
I told her that she'd seen
enough of the world

34:29.875 --> 34:30.834
and I'd had
enough nights alone.

34:30.917 --> 34:33.291
It was time for her to be
back where she belongs.

34:35.208 --> 34:37.792
Well, uh, Dad,
why don't you finalize

34:37.875 --> 34:39.333
those invitations, yeah?

34:39.417 --> 34:41.417
-Good.
-All right.

34:41.500 --> 34:44.041
I got to be
somewhere, so...

34:46.166 --> 34:49.333
Those are the certs
on the 4140,

34:49.417 --> 34:53.208
the high strength-low alloy,
and the nickel chromium.

34:53.291 --> 34:57.458
And here is
your rightful compensation.

34:57.542 --> 35:00.500
♪ dramatic music ♪

35:00.583 --> 35:03.458
Take him.

35:03.542 --> 35:06.291
Let's talk about next
month's chromium vanadium.

35:06.375 --> 35:08.000
Your
stuff's not bad.

35:08.083 --> 35:09.166
Well, it's
gonna look much better

35:09.250 --> 35:10.291
after you're done
with it.

35:10.375 --> 35:11.709
NYPD.

35:11.792 --> 35:12.917
Keep your hands
where I can see them.

35:13.000 --> 35:14.417
Cuff him.
Get him out of here.

35:14.500 --> 35:15.917
-Wait, wait, wait.
-Keep your hands

35:16.000 --> 35:17.166
-where I can see them!
-Hey! Quiet.

35:17.250 --> 35:18.834
What the fuck is
going on Jack!

35:18.917 --> 35:20.125
Okay. You can
stop recording.

35:20.208 --> 35:21.667
Did you
set this up, Jack?!

35:21.750 --> 35:25.959
♪ dramatic music ♪

35:26.041 --> 35:28.041
-Sir.
-Give him the space, boys.

35:28.125 --> 35:29.500
♪♪♪

35:29.583 --> 35:33.041
Chuck.

35:33.125 --> 35:33.625
No.

35:33.709 --> 35:36.959
Yes, Jack.

35:37.041 --> 35:38.417
Looks like you just
got your manhood

35:38.500 --> 35:40.041
caught in a tiger trap...

35:41.625 --> 35:43.834
I know that you have built
a good chunk of your fortune

35:43.917 --> 35:46.834
on cheap steel deals.

35:46.917 --> 35:48.834
It's a helluva scheme.

35:48.917 --> 35:52.375
I admire its grift
and effectiveness.

35:52.458 --> 35:53.208
You import
the sub-par goods,

35:53.291 --> 35:54.750
get your man
at the ratings agency

35:54.834 --> 35:57.125
to mark it high grade,

35:57.208 --> 35:59.208
sell it into state-run
projects at top dollar.

35:59.291 --> 36:01.667
The problem is:
it's not only illegal,

36:01.750 --> 36:04.792
it's fucking dangerous,

36:04.875 --> 36:07.959
and someone is
gonna get hurt.

36:08.041 --> 36:10.417
Imagine what people
would say if they learned

36:10.500 --> 36:12.417
that the new bridges
and rails they ride on

36:12.500 --> 36:14.875
were built
of inferior stuff.

36:14.959 --> 36:16.625
And if they had cause
to look back

36:16.709 --> 36:17.875
through your past
municipal works,

36:17.959 --> 36:22.625
well  the fallout
from that in terms of liability

36:22.709 --> 36:25.583
could bankrupt an Astor.

36:25.667 --> 36:27.583
What are you doing...

36:27.667 --> 36:29.375
Hmm?

36:29.458 --> 36:30.625
Just what are you doing?

36:31.792 --> 36:35.583
You know, it's a good thing
that this is my operation,

36:35.667 --> 36:38.083
and I alone have
the discretion

36:38.166 --> 36:41.125
to move forward
in processing and prosecuting

36:41.208 --> 36:43.083
the felons involved...

36:43.166 --> 36:47.542
or I can take
a more tempered approach.

36:49.417 --> 36:52.792
Now's certainly not the time
for hasty decisions.

36:52.875 --> 36:54.792
No. No, it's not.

36:56.875 --> 36:58.625
♪♪♪

36:58.709 --> 37:02.667
But now is the time
to set new terms.

37:02.750 --> 37:06.458
Things will be different
moving forward.

37:06.542 --> 37:09.125
I will take your counsel--
but that's all it will be.

37:09.208 --> 37:10.500
I will make
the decisions.

37:10.583 --> 37:14.166
You and your people
work for me.

37:14.250 --> 37:15.959
Is that clear?

37:17.208 --> 37:19.750
Clear as Catskills
spring water...

37:22.166 --> 37:24.458
Damned impressive, Chuck.

37:24.542 --> 37:27.000
It was frightening as hell
for a moment there.

37:27.083 --> 37:29.875
But, uh, it was
damned impressive.

37:33.458 --> 37:35.917
Downright gubernatorial...

37:59.625 --> 38:00.500
Did it go well?

38:00.583 --> 38:04.000
Well, as well as it
could've, operationally.

38:04.083 --> 38:05.834
It never feels good
doing that to a man.

38:05.917 --> 38:08.166
Even a man like Foley.

38:08.250 --> 38:10.625
I need a Silkwood shower
right about now.

38:10.709 --> 38:13.583
It'll have to wait.
You have a visitor.

38:19.834 --> 38:21.417
Judge.

38:21.500 --> 38:24.500
Wonderful to see you.

38:24.583 --> 38:26.291
Last time I was here...
pretty momentous.

38:26.375 --> 38:29.125
I thought we were
never to talk of it.

38:29.208 --> 38:31.125
We're gonna talk
about everything.

38:31.959 --> 38:34.500
Where are we starting?

38:34.583 --> 38:36.208
With bracing honesty.

38:36.291 --> 38:37.667
Because with all
that's passed between us.

38:37.750 --> 38:40.000
I see no reason
to beat about the bush.

38:40.083 --> 38:41.542
Begin.

38:43.375 --> 38:44.583
Right here,
in this house,

38:44.667 --> 38:48.458
you put me on a path that
leads to the Supreme Court.

38:49.792 --> 38:53.041
Well, it's not exactly
a straight and easy one.

38:53.125 --> 38:54.542
There's turns and twists

38:54.625 --> 38:58.041
and highwaymen
hiding in the bushes

38:58.125 --> 38:59.542
who might jump you
at any time.

38:59.625 --> 39:02.709
I agree. The path
is treacherous.

39:04.166 --> 39:05.250
Which is why I need you
to guide me.

39:05.333 --> 39:08.291
As I have and will
continue to do.

39:08.375 --> 39:11.417
From your current
perch, yes.

39:11.500 --> 39:15.208
But if you leave office,
to go after another,

39:15.291 --> 39:18.583
my flank
is unprotected.

39:18.667 --> 39:20.750
I will give you
all the support

39:20.834 --> 39:24.250
and assistance you need
from Albany.

39:24.333 --> 39:26.333
Not good enough,
I'm afraid.

39:27.792 --> 39:29.125
I see.

39:30.583 --> 39:33.083
I'm here to ask you to honor
your promise to me:

39:36.000 --> 39:38.125
that there was
no favor you'd refuse.

39:38.208 --> 39:40.291
Well, you will have to
state the favor, directly.

39:40.375 --> 39:43.291
I need you to stay
U.S. Attorney.

39:43.375 --> 39:47.208
♪ dramatic music ♪

39:47.291 --> 39:50.375
Ah, man.

39:50.458 --> 39:51.959
♪♪♪

39:57.125 --> 39:58.458
I've set my sights
on governor.

39:58.542 --> 40:00.875
I have bled
for this caper.

40:00.959 --> 40:03.417
There must be another way
to help you get over.

40:03.500 --> 40:04.792
There isn't.

40:04.875 --> 40:07.000
If you're gone, AG Jeffcoat
will appoint someone new,

40:07.083 --> 40:08.250
someone who won't
give a shit about me.

40:08.333 --> 40:09.625
Or the kinds
of cases I need.

40:09.709 --> 40:14.417
Or worse, back another judge
and bury me in garbage.

40:14.500 --> 40:15.959
I can't let you go.

40:16.041 --> 40:19.625
♪♪♪

40:19.709 --> 40:21.667
I understand it isn't
convenient for you,

40:21.750 --> 40:24.875
but it wasn't convenient
for me to help you either...

40:24.959 --> 40:26.792
♪♪♪

40:26.875 --> 40:31.834
The shit I have done to
position myself for this...

40:31.917 --> 40:34.792
Among those things:
your oath to me.

40:37.417 --> 40:41.375
I'm gonna need the night
before I can give you an answer.

40:43.709 --> 40:45.125
I imagine you do.

40:45.208 --> 40:49.834
♪♪♪

40:49.917 --> 40:52.000
Each time I'm here,
I'm more and more impressed

40:52.083 --> 40:53.166
with the warmth
of your home

40:53.250 --> 40:57.792
and the life
you've built.

40:57.875 --> 40:59.625
It speaks
to your character.

41:19.083 --> 41:21.041
You are considering it.

41:21.959 --> 41:23.667
It seemed the least
that I could do.

41:26.125 --> 41:28.166
But I'm gonna
tell him no.

41:28.250 --> 41:30.166
I mean, I've committed--
I've committed

41:30.250 --> 41:32.792
too much thought and energy
to this governor thing.

41:39.041 --> 41:41.375
♪ tense music ♪

41:41.458 --> 41:42.709
What about passion?

41:44.333 --> 41:45.250
Excitement.

41:45.333 --> 41:47.458
What about fire?

41:47.542 --> 41:50.041
I see those things
on your face

41:50.125 --> 41:52.625
every day you go
to work at Southern.

41:55.667 --> 41:58.291
I always have. It's one
of the things I love about you.

41:58.375 --> 42:00.083
No matter how difficult
the situation,

42:00.166 --> 42:05.000
how fucked it seems you are,
you relish the fight.

42:05.083 --> 42:06.583
As long as there's
any game left,

42:06.667 --> 42:08.041
you play it
'til the very end.

42:08.125 --> 42:09.083
Full out.

42:09.166 --> 42:12.083
♪♪♪

42:12.166 --> 42:15.625
And why wouldn't that be
the case with the governorship?

42:15.709 --> 42:17.750
Politics is a different
kind of fight.

42:17.834 --> 42:21.583
It's about consensus building
and concession granting

42:21.667 --> 42:24.458
and hand wringing
and ass kissing.

42:24.542 --> 42:28.834
But in your job now,
you are a king.

42:30.417 --> 42:33.250
You engage the battles
you choose.

42:33.333 --> 42:35.583
In the manner
you choose.

42:35.667 --> 42:38.333
You decide what's right
and what's wrong.

42:38.417 --> 42:39.583
With no one to appease.

42:39.667 --> 42:42.792
Well, you're forgetting
Jock Jeffcoat.

42:42.875 --> 42:46.792
He's a more powerful king,
for the moment.

42:46.875 --> 42:47.959
You've deposed
his kind before.

42:48.041 --> 42:52.333
Look what you just did to
Jack Foley. And can do again.

42:54.333 --> 42:58.125
You don't want
to be in politics,

42:58.208 --> 42:58.959
you want to be
beyond politics.

42:59.041 --> 43:01.959
♪♪♪

43:02.041 --> 43:04.667
I am all in
for you, Chuck.

43:04.750 --> 43:06.375
But I can't turn off
the part of me

43:06.458 --> 43:07.959
that does the job I do.

43:08.041 --> 43:11.041
And looking at you,

43:11.125 --> 43:14.709
I see someone

43:14.792 --> 43:17.208
who knows that
one of those things

43:17.291 --> 43:20.500
makes them feel
truly alive.

43:20.583 --> 43:23.125
And that the other is gonna
feel like an obligation.

43:23.208 --> 43:25.500
♪ pensive music ♪

43:27.542 --> 43:31.583
♪♪♪

43:44.291 --> 43:45.458
I figured it'd last...

43:45.542 --> 43:48.417
The feeling
of exhilaration?

43:48.500 --> 43:50.667
Of winning. Last
longer than a day.

43:50.750 --> 43:52.375
Did you even get
a full day?

43:52.458 --> 43:54.542
The initial jolt
when it all worked out

43:54.625 --> 43:57.083
and the judge gaveled it--
that was pretty good.

43:57.166 --> 43:58.333
Felt like I was doing
220 miles an hour

43:58.417 --> 43:59.750
on a dirt bike in Moab

43:59.834 --> 44:04.208
and skidded to a stop
just before the cliff.

44:04.291 --> 44:06.542
But then it ended
and there was nothing.

44:06.625 --> 44:08.583
So no.

44:10.417 --> 44:13.291
You know, I thought
that a battle of the kind

44:13.375 --> 44:16.041
that we just fought
could truly be won.

44:16.125 --> 44:18.333
I beat the case.
I'm back here trading.

44:18.417 --> 44:20.000
I'll be around
for my boys--

44:20.083 --> 44:22.000
-We need to talk about Gordie--
-We do.

44:22.083 --> 44:25.041
There's residual damage.
He's part of it.

44:25.125 --> 44:26.709
Can that ever
be undone?

44:26.792 --> 44:26.917
No.

44:29.166 --> 44:30.625
We're all scarred.

44:30.709 --> 44:33.458
Yeah. I thought scar tissue
was supposed to be stronger.

44:33.542 --> 44:36.083
That's actually medically
untrue, it's just rougher.

44:36.166 --> 44:37.792
Well, I liked it
better the other way.

44:37.875 --> 44:40.333
Yeah. Well.
Sure. Me too.

44:45.375 --> 44:46.834
Then what do you
got for me?

44:48.000 --> 44:52.208
I can't help but feel that
whatever advice I offer you,

44:52.291 --> 44:54.208
or Chuck for that matter,
now, is colored

44:54.291 --> 44:56.500
by what we've all
been through and done.

44:57.709 --> 45:00.291
It's less pure.
As am I.

45:00.375 --> 45:01.667
Because of Mafee?

45:01.750 --> 45:02.500
For one.

45:02.583 --> 45:05.375
I set him up
really good.

45:05.458 --> 45:07.667
Got his loyalty going
for as long as I needed it.

45:07.750 --> 45:08.917
Look, give yourself
a pass on that.

45:09.000 --> 45:12.417
It barely registers as bad,
the world I come from.

45:12.500 --> 45:15.250
I'm not sure I can.

45:15.333 --> 45:18.250
♪ pensive music ♪

45:18.333 --> 45:21.375
Okay. Let me give you
some advice for a change.

45:21.458 --> 45:22.709
Maybe I'll take it too:

45:22.792 --> 45:26.333
you can sit here killing
yourself if you want,

45:26.417 --> 45:30.792
but when you do something
to put yourself back in charge,

45:30.875 --> 45:32.625
remind yourself
that you are not less,

45:32.709 --> 45:34.709
but more powerful for
what you've come through--

45:34.792 --> 45:37.417
that's when
you'll feel better.

45:37.500 --> 45:41.125
♪♪♪

45:41.208 --> 45:43.917
♪♪♪

45:49.542 --> 45:50.625
What the fuck
is he doing here?

45:50.709 --> 45:51.834
We busted a cap
in his ass,

45:51.917 --> 45:52.333
we didn't just
give him the day off.

45:52.417 --> 45:54.792
I know, I know.

45:54.875 --> 45:57.834
And I can't believe
I'm fucking doing this,

45:57.917 --> 46:01.667
but I may have
been a bit hasty

46:01.750 --> 46:04.500
in the personal insult
and car wrecking departments...

46:04.583 --> 46:05.625
Ya think, Rickles?

46:05.709 --> 46:07.667
You called him a pants shitter
on the trading floor.

46:07.750 --> 46:08.500
Explain.

46:12.625 --> 46:15.125
I have to tell you
that Spyros here

46:15.208 --> 46:20.166
has...shared a unique...
investment strategy with me.

46:20.250 --> 46:22.166
One that is proprietary.

46:22.250 --> 46:26.458
Based on his prior...
work experience.

46:28.583 --> 46:30.333
Are you understanding
this gibberish?

46:30.417 --> 46:33.250
Yeah, I may be.

46:33.333 --> 46:36.417
And this...strategy,
you believe it'll pay off?

46:36.500 --> 46:38.125
I do.

46:38.208 --> 46:40.542
If we carefully
implement it,

46:40.625 --> 46:44.208
it can remove
certain...

46:44.291 --> 46:47.709
doubt, endemic
to the market.

46:47.792 --> 46:48.959
Is this
a renewable source?

46:49.041 --> 46:51.458
As long as we don't 'open
our proverbial overcoats'

46:51.542 --> 46:53.917
and 'flash our junk'

46:54.000 --> 46:56.583
at a particular
three-lettered agency.

46:58.375 --> 47:00.375
As long as we
play it cool.

47:00.458 --> 47:01.542
Right.

47:05.542 --> 47:08.375
Alright, Spyros.

47:08.458 --> 47:11.709
You may have provided
additional value.

47:11.792 --> 47:15.208
I'm gonna give you a second
shot at Wilbury status.

47:15.291 --> 47:17.166
"Handle me with care."

47:18.834 --> 47:19.291
Pound it out.

47:19.375 --> 47:21.458
No.

47:27.166 --> 47:28.959
Still not a fucking Wilbury.

47:29.041 --> 47:30.458
Not even close.

47:31.500 --> 47:34.083
♪ funky music ♪

47:34.166 --> 47:38.709
♪♪♪

47:38.792 --> 47:42.959
♪♪♪

47:46.166 --> 47:48.709
Kids are being driven
to the restaurant.

47:48.792 --> 47:52.000
Good, I'll be leaving shortly
when I finish up here.

47:52.083 --> 47:52.834
So...?

47:52.917 --> 47:55.834
I've thought
about it, and, uh,

47:55.917 --> 47:58.583
I'm ready to give you
a discount on the fees.

47:58.667 --> 47:59.834
Discount?

47:59.917 --> 48:04.166
If you sign an agreement--
a seven year lock up.

48:04.250 --> 48:05.750
-On the money.
-Mm-hmm.

48:05.834 --> 48:08.417
1.5 and 15. It's not
the discount you wanted--

48:08.500 --> 48:09.375
which, by the way,
I give to nobody.

48:09.458 --> 48:11.667
But it's the best discount
